<DOC><DOCNO> AP890808-0169 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-08-89 2214EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-AIDSChild     08-08 0238</FIRST><SECOND>AM-AIDS Child,0243</SECOND><HEAD>Authorities: Young AIDS Patient Victim of Sexual Abuse, Drug Injections</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 9-year-old girl contracted AIDS by beingsexually abused by her mother and was reportedly injected withdrugs as punishment, state social workers said.   The girl has been taken into custody by the state and placed infoster care with a family who knows her, said David Reilly,regional director of the Texas Department of Human Services.   ``From everything we can determine from the circumstances, itappears to be she got it (AIDS) from abuse,'' he said Monday.   ``Everybody just wants to give her the best we can give her inthe time she has,'' Reilly said. ``She is with the person she wantsto be with and if that works out, there is no reason to move her.''   The girl's mother, a drug abuser, died of acquired immunedeficiency syndrome. Social workers believe she is the person whosexually abused the girl and gave her drug injections as a form ofpunishment.   Authorities held a closed-door hearing Monday concerning thegirl. District Judge Tom Rickhoff said the hearing was closedbecause of a law requiring confidentiality in AIDS cases.   After her mother's death, the girl was left to live withrelatives. Social workers were concerned those surroundings werefurther endangering her life, so they obtained an emergency courtorder to remove the girl and place her in foster care.</TEXT></DOC>